            <Text>An eternal perspective from Jesus. What is real. Jesus said my kingdom is not of this world. Train your mind to distinguish between a temporal fact and an eternal reality. 

I search for truth 

The course and Urantia book give us some pretty exciting possibilities if we want to push our mental training beyond current norms. The Course says forgiveness is the key to accessing the higher mind functions. The UB gives us plenty of information to help us understand what can happen should we push deeper into the superconscious. It gives us warnings and encouragement. Transcending our current conscious state was much further out of reach before these two books were available. Now we have an instruction book to show us the way. Pursue a path few have had the opportunity to pursue. 

We know from reading the Urantia book that it is possible to transcend this temporal reality and effect fusion with pure spirit reality, the indwelling divine monitor. This is more exciting than exploring space as an astronaut. And potentially much more rewarding. I suspect some have penetrated deep into the morontia realm of mind and are helping our celestial friends in what ever way they can. 

The Urantia book says our minds are not altogether limited by time. We do have the ability within our minds to seek eternal truths. It requires mind training. The Course offers us mind training from the eternal perspective. 

Appeal directly to the diving spirit within. 
So many have benefited from a Course in Miracles. Recently I listened to a testimony on youtube of someone who turned her life around after studying the Course in Miracles. Could it be that those who are open to hearing an appeal to the spirit within will benefit from the Course? Is Jesus making an appeal to our spirit within, directly to our thought adjuster? 

159:3.2 While emotion as a factor in human decisions cannot be wholly eliminated, it should not be directly appealed to in the teachings of those who would advance the cause of the kingdom. MAKE YOUR APPEALS DIRECTLY TO THE DIVINE SPIRIT THAT DWELLS WITHIN THE MINDS OF MEN. Do not appeal to fear, pity, or mere sentiment. 

Our thoughts of others
We cannot love God more than we love each other. It is built into the plan of creation. How do I look at each person I interact with? Am I judging, critical? Do I project my problems out into the world? Or do I project the deeper truths I want to see into the world? There can be no middle ground. If we love we see love and are loved. If we are critical, we see bad behavior everywhere. If we are judgmental we see guilt in everyone. It is a simple formula. Practice until it becomes clear. Free yourself. 

